## Re: EC / RATE REQUEST / SEPTEMBER 2H / NOR SHIPMENTS STARCARGO

受信日時: Sat Sep 06 2025 06:09:56 GMT+0800 (Singapore Standard Time)  
From: Adriana Naula \<adriana.naula@one-line.com\>  
To: Kazuki Masuda \<kazuki.masuda@one-line.com\>  
Dear Masuda san,

Thank you for your proposal. I wanted to share some insights regarding

Starcargo's business.

While they have experienced significant growth with most carriers this

year, we haven't seen the same with ONE during the 2025\.

\[image: image.png\]

For over two years, we have limited our space commitment to NORs mainly.

This decision was made to address a specific need, help us achieve our NOR

targets, and increase our reefer inventory for our exports. However, we

haven't yet explored opportunities with GP containers. This limitation is

currently working against us, especially this year, as other carriers are

increasingly seeking NOR business from Starcargo. Our rates have also been

above their target for several consecutive months and there have been some

cancellations because of that. With this it's not my intention to say that

we will lose the account but I do believe we are jeopardizing some

businesses they currently handle with ONE. I also understand this is just

not about the rate but the complete service we offer to them but the

targets shared are not meant to take advantage of our rate but getting in

the same line as other carriers are offering to Starcargo. We also need to
